@node Introduction "PostScript PlugIn: Introduction"

                                  Introduction
                                 --------------

PostScript-Print is a Printer-PlugIn for the famous Image-Manipulation-Program
ArtEffect2+. As a normal PlugIn it integrates seamlessly in ArtEffect's menu
and waits happily for your attention.

It is able to produces PostScript files which are suitable for printing
directly or placing (with EPS on) in a program such as PageStream3.

It is mainly written to print pictures directly out of ArtEffect to a PostScript
printer or to save on disk for later printing or placing.

Since no other Amiga program (except my @{" dt2ps " link dt2ps} (AFAIK)) produces
such small output files, printing is normally faster than with any other
program. Because the parallel port of Amiga (and even most I/O-Cards) is slow
and the main bottleneck for any recent printer.

@endnode

@node Features "PostScript PlugIn: Features"

                                    Features
                                   ----------

- AFAIK the second program (first was dt2ps) for Amiga that uses RunLength- and
  the efficient ASCII85Encoding to reduce the size of the PostScript file

- Output can be made for printing directly or placing in e.g. PageStream3

- Gammacorrection for pictures

- Interpolation to smooth pictures can be switched on

- Takes advantage of picture's alphachannel

- Output can be color or gray (with two different color-to-gray conversions)

- Setting frequency and angle and spotfunction for output raster by user   or

- Automatic calculation of optimal rasterfrequency

- 12 different spotfunctions included

- Autofit, Autorientation ...



@endnode

